What *really* put this over the edge for me was the large number of very detailed descriptions of the horrific things people saw.

People talk about vague amorphous scary stuff, but these were acute, and particular, and very detailed.

Aside from that, I have to echo a lot of what ARD said: This was tight, and well paced. Nothing felt wasted, and every section felt like it explored and explained what it was talking about, then finished before it felt overplayed. A good example being the initial bulleted list of entities. Enough to really get my skin crawling, but just enough that I felt like  without feeling like it wasn't enough.

Really, really good stuff man.







